{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/cpp-variables","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"22ab454a-6813-5e82-ad30-03588f044a64","html":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#anatomy-of-a-variable\">Anatomy of a Variable</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#basic-data-types\">Basic Data Types</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#variables-in-action\">Variables in Action</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#references\">References</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"anatomy-of-a-variable\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#anatomy-of-a-variable\" aria-label=\"anatomy of a variable permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Anatomy of a Variable</h2>\n<p>Let’s take a look at an example.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">int ourVariable = 42;</code></pre></div>\n<p>We can see 3 parts on the variable declaration.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">int</code> - this is our <em>data type</em></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">ourVariable</code> - this is the name of the variable</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">42</code> - this is the <em>initial value</em> of the variable</li>\n</ol>\n<p>All variable names must:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Begin with a letter or an underscore ”_“.</li>\n<li>Spaces and special characters are not allowed.</li>\n<li>Must <strong>not</strong> be a <a href=\"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/keyword\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">reserved word</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"basic-data-types\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#basic-data-types\" aria-label=\"basic data types permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basic Data Types</h2>\n<p>Also called <strong>Primitive Data Types</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>void - holds <strong>nothing</strong></li>\n<li>bool - holds <strong>true</strong> or <strong>false</strong></li>\n<li>int - holds <strong>whole numbers</strong></li>\n<li>float - holds <strong>numbers with decimals</strong></li>\n<li>double - holds <strong>numbers with decimals</strong></li>\n<li>char - holds <strong>single characters</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"variables-in-action\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#variables-in-action\" aria-label=\"variables in action permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Variables in Action</h2>\n<p>You can use variables in C++ as like a variable in math. You can save a value on them in order to recall it later and/or multiple times. See the example below:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">#include &lt;iostream&gt;\n\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n    int variable1 = 12;\n    char myLetter = &#39;G&#39;;\n    std::cout &lt;&lt; variable1 &lt;&lt; std::endl;\n    std::cout &lt;&lt; myLetter &lt;&lt; std::endl;\n\n    return 0;\n}</code></pre></div>\n<p>Expected Output:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">12\nG</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#related\" aria-label=\"related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/cpp-if-statements\">If Statements</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cpp-hello-world\">Hello World</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"references\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>References</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/What-are-primitive-data-type-in-Cplusplus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.tutorialspoint.com/What-are-primitive-data-type-in-Cplusplus</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/keyword\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/keyword</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/cpp-variables","tagSlugs":["/tag/c/","/tag/tutorial/","/tag/variables/","/tag/data-types/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-09-11T12:50:03","description":"Variables in C++ are declared with \"DataType varName = value;\". The name of the variable can be anyting you want while putting the value during declaration is optional.","tags":["C++","Tutorial","Variables","Data Types"],"title":"Variables and Data Types","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/cpp-variables"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","3942705351","401334301"]}